HEADWORD: Concertante
<hw>Con`cer*tan"te</hw> <pr>(?; It. ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.,
orig p. pr. of <ets>concertare</ets> to form or perform a concert. See
<er>Concert</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A concert for two or
more principal instruments, with orchestral accompaniment. Also
adjectively; <as>as, <ex>concertante</ex> parts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concertation</ent>⟦br⟧
